</m:mrow>
</m:mfrac>
</m:mtd>
</m:mtr>
</m:mtable>
</m:math>
</para>
<para id="element-37">Now, the magnitude of angular momentum is given by :
</para>
<para id="element-38">
<m:math display="block">
<m:mtable columnalign="left">
<m:mtr>
<m:mtd>
<m:mi> ℓ </m:mi>
<m:mo> = </m:mo> 
<m:mi> m </m:mi>
<m:mi> v </m:mi>
<m:mi> r </m:mi>
</m:mtd>
</m:mtr>
</m:mtable>
</m:math>
</para>
<para id="element-39">
Squaring both sides, we have :
</para>
<para id="element-40">
<m:math display="block">
<m:mtable columnalign="left">
<m:mtr>
<m:mtd>
<m:mo> ⇒ </m:mo> 
<m:msup>
<m:mi> ℓ </m:mi>
